.TH "amdgpu_ttm_access_memory" 9 "amdgpu_ttm_access_memory" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
amdgpu_ttm_access_memory \- Read or Write memory that backs a buffer object.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" amdgpu_ttm_access_memory
.BI "(struct ttm_buffer_object *bo "  ","
.BI "unsigned long offset "  ","
.BI "void *buf "  ","
.BI "int len "  ","
.BI "int write "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bo" 12
The buffer object to read/write
.IP "offset" 12
Offset into buffer object
.IP "buf" 12
Secondary buffer to write/read from
.IP "len" 12
Length in bytes of access
.IP "write" 12
true if writing
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is used to access VRAM that backs a buffer object via MMIO
access for debugging purposes.
